00:00:03.649 --> 00:00:05.520
How to Choose Rum.

00:00:05.520 --> 00:00:09.260
Rum is available in a wide variety of weights,
ages, and blends.

00:00:09.260 --> 00:00:14.410
If you aspire to become a connoisseur of fine
rums, start with the basics.

00:00:14.410 --> 00:00:20.550
You will need Variety of rums Tasting events
or seminars Internet access and glass with

00:00:20.550 --> 00:00:22.030
a wide mouth.

00:00:22.030 --> 00:00:23.030
Step 1.

00:00:23.030 --> 00:00:24.619
Learn what rum isn’t.

00:00:24.619 --> 00:00:29.840
Unlike single malt Scotch, for example, environmental
conditions like climate and soil have little

00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:32.320
to do with rum variations.

00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:35.910
Rums vary due to methods of production, aging,
and blending.

00:00:35.910 --> 00:00:37.790
Rum ages much faster than Scotch whiskey.

00:00:37.790 --> 00:00:43.570
A five-year-old bottle of rum can be the age
equivalent of a 15-year-old Scotch.

00:00:43.570 --> 00:00:44.580
Step 2.

00:00:44.580 --> 00:00:48.710
Learn what rum is − rums are sugarcane or
molasses based.

00:00:48.710 --> 00:00:55.530
Rum classifications include white rum, dark
rum, golden rum, spiced rum, and blended aged

00:00:55.530 --> 00:00:56.530
rum.

00:00:56.530 --> 00:00:57.530
Step 3.

00:00:57.530 --> 00:00:59.510
Learn the differences between rums.

00:00:59.510 --> 00:01:04.430
White rums are the most popular and are used
typically with mixers; golden rums can be

00:01:04.430 --> 00:01:09.360
sipped; dark rums are typically molasses based;
and blended rums are made from a selection

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:11.440
of rums of varying vintages.

00:01:11.440 --> 00:01:18.130
Spiced rums can include ingredients like ginger,
allspice, cloves, vanilla, cinnamon, cherry,

00:01:18.130 --> 00:01:21.060
mint, and edible plant bark.

00:01:21.060 --> 00:01:22.060
Step 4.

00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:24.860
Learn the differences between rum production
processes.

00:01:24.860 --> 00:01:29.750
Some white rum is filtered multiple times
in column stills for a smoother taste; aged

00:01:29.750 --> 00:01:34.620
rum can take on the flavor of barrels previously
used for other substances.

00:01:34.620 --> 00:01:35.620
Step 5.

00:01:35.620 --> 00:01:38.040
Attend a rum-tasting event or seminar.

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:42.270
Taste rums from different producers, and visit
the Ministry of Rum website for their list

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:44.190
of tasting events and rum festivals.

00:01:44.190 --> 00:01:48.670
First-time rum drinkers should start with
a mixed drink, such as a daiquiri or a Mai

00:01:48.670 --> 00:01:49.670
Tai.

00:01:49.670 --> 00:01:50.670
Step 6.

00:01:50.670 --> 00:01:53.050
Learn how to properly taste rum.

00:01:53.050 --> 00:01:58.090
Tasting begins with smelling the aroma above
the glass rim, then smelling below the rim,

00:01:58.090 --> 00:02:01.290
sticking your nose into the glass, for full
aroma.

00:02:01.290 --> 00:02:05.740
Then take a small sip and breathe in through
your mouth as the rum washes over your tongue;

00:02:05.740 --> 00:02:06.910
swallow slowly.

00:02:06.910 --> 00:02:13.299
Did you know Mount Gay, from Barbados, began
making rum in 1663, making them the world’s

00:02:13.299 --> 00:02:14.959
oldest operating rum producer.

